column13: 99% ice at gauge, open leads on both banks.
column14: FT2 measurement ~1km d/s at d/s end of gravel bar with debris jam on it. Measured at 0.5 depth for time management, only 19 panels done for same reason, all under 10% Q. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Unable to locate control BM2. Surveyed from new BM BC2021-511, adjustment likely needed to DWL and MGH based on next full levels in Spring. Used listed elevation for BM and DID NOT reset the logger as this is likely still the best information we have for now (based on control BM2). One WL collected, used for MGH as the mmt is not used for curve building. Mid-section
